How Did REST Come To Mean The Opposite of REST In the essay &ldquo;How Did REST Come To Mean The Opposite of REST?&ldquo;1 the author advocates for what he explains as the original notion of REST output, as distinct from HTTP requests. He probably favors XML, too, for its self-documenting features. This article immediately ran counter to my principles, though: in particular, by combining data and display he runs counter to the separation of content and display that has made CSS good.